column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Walmet is missing a Mystel.
Speak with the missing Mystel.
Aid the missing Mystel.
Retrieve the sopping sacks of supplies.
Deliver the sopping sacks of supplies to the missing Mystel.
Speak with the missing Mystel.
Where is that Mystel? He should have been back by now...
I sent one of our newcomers to retrieve the supplies we had chilling in the river, and he has yet to return. I hope he hasn't run into trouble with the local dwarf clan...
If your travels take you in that direction, could you keep an eye out for our missing Mystel?
The newcomer─I've forgotten his name─was only meant to grab the sacks we had chilling upriver, then come straight back. I hope nothing bad has befallen him...
Can't...<gasp>...breathe...
The Mystel appears in need of a solid pat on the back.
<pant> <pant> Phew...
Th-Thank you! I think...<huff>...I can breathe again...

I was just on my way back to the village when some Goggs started yelling at me. They were certainly cross about something, so I just ran away as fast as my feet would carry me...in the wrong direction, as it turns out.
Before I knew it, I'd collapsed here on the riverbank and dropped all my sacks into the water. They must've floated downstream, but I'm still...<puff>...too buggered...to go look for them...
Ugh, my chest...<huff>...is still heaving... I hope those sacks...<gasp>...don't get washed...over the falls...
Oh...are those my sacks?
I must say, this is a welcome relief! Let's just take a quick peek inside to see that everything's still─
Bah, I knew it! Only the wine's missing, and that means dwarves. They must've followed me...
Well, I'd best hurry home before I cross paths with them again. You should come too─no good deed should go unrewarded, after all!
Thank you again for your help. If you'd not found me, I might have fallen prey to some wild beast─or worse, a party of wine-drunk Goggs.
If only they were more like the Tholls. At least we can live alongside <Emphasis>those</Emphasis> dwarves in some semblance of harmony.
Anyway, here's the reward I promised you!
Thank you for finding our wayward Mystel. Were it not for you, he may have fallen in after the supplies and been washed away downriver!
